<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Takes China Soccer Title in Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Dalian Wanda
defeated Guangzhou Apollo two goals against nil to take the title
of the Chinese Soccer League on Thursday with five rounds remained.
</P>
<P>
Wanda improved its unbeaten record to 51 and won its third
title as the league entered its fourth year stage.
</P>
<P>
From 14 wins and three draws, Wanda has scored 45 points after
the 17th round, 16 points clear of second placer Shanghai Shenhua.
</P>
<P>
Wanda dominated the game by scoring the first in the 28th
minute when Wang Tao curled an angled free-kick on the brink of
the box.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes before the break, Hao Haidong, top scorer with 11
in the league, chested down the pass from Wang Tao before an
Apollo defender tapped in an own goal.
</P>
<P>
Wanda kept its momentum in the pitch but failed to extend the
lead with poor finishes in the second half.
</P>
<P>
In Chongqing, Yanbian Aodong capitalised on its rare chance to
beat host Vanguards Huandao with a goal at the 88th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Vanguards played an excellent match with most possession of
the ball but all their shots turned into vain.
</P>
<P>
Strikers Gaofeng and Han Jinming forced Aodong's goalkeeper to
dive to and from to block the string of attacks before Li Canjie
scored the lone late goal in a peculiar counterattack.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Tianjin Samsung exploited its home advantage
to share one point with powerhouse Shanghai Shenhua as neither
side opened the account in the regular 90-minute competition.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Hongyuan also had to settle for a scoreless draw with
Jinan Taishan, while Sichuan Quanxing drew with August First 2-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
