<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Royal Bank Sets Profit Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Royal Bank of Canada earned
a record 1.68 billion dollars (1.18 billion US dollars) in fiscal
1997, the highest annual profit in Canadian corporate history,
said reports today.
</P>
<P>
The earnings were 17 percent higher than last year's 1.43
billion dollars. The bank's also set a profit record in the fourth
quarter, earning 449 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Royal's record profit came as a result of its strong
performances from all its operations, and particularly stock
market related, fee-based businesses, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
So far, four of Canada's Big Six banks have reported their
earnings in the fiscal year ended October 31.
</P>
<P>
The collective 1997 profit for the four banks were 5.56 billion
dollars, up 21 percent from last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
