<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Sees More Vehicles Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Canada's auto sales went up 15
percent last month, the highest November levels since 1989, said
reports today.
</P>
<P>
Sales of cars, trucks and minivans jumped to 109,603 during the
month from 95,235 a year ago. The industry racked up sales of
112,714 in November 1989.
</P>
<P>
For the first 11 months of the year, sales totaled 1.261
million, surpassing the total of 1.173 million recorded in all of
1996 and a 16-percent jump on the sales in the first 11 months of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Auto sales for 1997 are on pace to exceed 1.35 million, which
would be the best year for the industry since 1989, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
As has been the case for much of the year, huge gains in truck
sales have more than compensated for weak car sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
