<HEADLINE> Uganda Textile Mill to Double Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- African Textile Mill (ATM) in
eastern Uganda is expected to double its output in the future,
Rao Kalluri, the General Manager of Mbale-based ATM, said.
</P>
<P>
Kalluri said his factory is heading to become the best of its
kind in Africa, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
He said his factory has installed the fourth machine to
increase its product to 12,000 or 13,000 meters of cotton fabric
every day from its 5,000 or 6,000 meters a month earlier, an
increase of 100 percent compared with previous years.
</P>
<P>
The fourth machine will operate in December, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Kalluri told the local English newspaper ''the Monitor'' that
Cooperative Bank has offered a loan to help his factory expand
its capacity of producing 18 million meters and up to 2,000 tons
of yarn a year for export. But he did not say how much he had
got from the bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
