<HEADLINE> Durban Prepares for Influx of Holiday-makers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The well-known port city
of Durban in South Africa is making preparation for the influx of
holiday-makers during the coming peak of holiday season, the city
authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 people have been employed for the season,
additional police satellite stations erected and increased marine
safety procedures implemented to meet the needs of tourists, the
city council told a press conference in Durban.
</P>
<P>
The influx of informal traders would be controlled and health
officials would monitor food sold by street vendors.
</P>
<P>
Traffic into and out of the beach front area would also be
controlled by police and traffic officials.
</P>
<P>
A joint police and security force would be operational 24
hours a day to cope with the situation, the council said.
</P>
</TEXT>
