<HEADLINE> Editorial: Developing Overall Friendly Cooperative Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- In an editorial to be published
Friday by the People's Daily hails the just-concluded state visits
by Chinese President Jiang Zemin to Canada and Mexico as a
complete success.
</P>
<P>
The leading Chinese official newspaper says, "The visits have
achieved the goals of deepening understanding, enhancing
friendship, looking forward to the future and developing
cooperation."
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Canadian Governor-General Romeo Leblanc
and Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo, President Jiang visited the
two countries from November 26 to December 3 and was warmly
welcomed and received by the two governments and two peoples.
</P>
<P>
This is another important diplomatic move made by China toward
the America after President Jiang paid a state visit to the United
States, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
China, Canada and Mexico, which are three major countries on
the Pacific and members of APEC, play a key role in promoting
peace, stability and development in the Asia-Pacific region and
the world at large, it says.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's tour of the two countries was a big event in the
history of the Sino-Canadian and Sino-Mexican relations, which
drew close attention from the Asia-Pacific and world media, it
adds.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that at the turn of century the positive results
achieved during Jiang's visits to Canada and Mexico will exert a
positive impact on establishing and developing a new type of
state-to-state relationship which conforms to the law of history
and the trend of times and on promoting the lofty cause of peace
and development of the human beings," it notes.
</P>
</TEXT>
