<HEADLINE> Germany Provides Grant Assistance to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Germany has agreed to provide
a grant assistance of some 22.2 million U.S. dollars to finance a
power renovation project in Nepal, Nepal's official RSS news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be used to cover the foreign exchange cost of the
electric and communication equipment for expanding the Load
Dispatch Center in Kathmandu, and to expand the Balaju sub-station
for the connection of two additional transmission lines to the
center.
</P>
<P>
The two lines will connect the Khimti Khola and Chilime
hydroelectric power plants to the network of Kathmandu and to the
Load Dispatch Center.
</P>
<P>
Once the center is expanded, supply interruptions due to
continuous check will be reduced and restoration of the supply
will be faster, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal and Germany have confirmed poverty alleviation as the
overall aim of their development cooperation, while developing
infrastructure is a priority area in Nepal's efforts to alleviate
poverty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
