<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Exploit Gold Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government
and the National Mining Corporation of Ethiopia today signed an
agreement to exploit gold mines.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the Ministry of Mines and Energy said the
accord gives the license to the national mining corporation an
exclusive right to explore gold and associated minerals in Werrii
area, northern Tigray region for the coming three years, which
covers 297.35 square kms.
</P>
<P>
The corporation will spend a minimum of 14,278,000 Birr (about
2.1 million U.S Dollars) during the three years of exploration
period and is expected to start activities within 45 days from
the signing of the pact, according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The pact was signed by Izaddin Ali, Minister of Mines and
Energy, and Melaku Beza, General Manager of the National Mining
Corporation of Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
