<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Editorial: Developing Overall Friendly Cooperative Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mexico, which has a culture of long standing, is a
developing country with significant influence in the Latin
American region.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and Mexican people have enjoyed a traditional
friendship which dates back to ancient times, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
Both countries have been subjected to humiliation by
colonialists in the modern times and have waged a long struggle
for national independence.
</P>
<P>
The editorial points out that China and Mexico have been
pursuing a peaceful foreign policy of independence and work for
the establishment of a new, peaceful, stable, just and reasonable
political and economic order in the world.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are now faced with the common tasks of
developing economy and improving people's well-being.
</P>
<P>
China and Mexico, which share a long history of friendship,
have a solid foundation for developing all-round cooperation, the
editorial notes.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Mexico, President Jiang and his Mexican
counterpart Ernesto Zedillo agreed to establish an all-round
partnership oriented to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have reached a number of agreements on bilateral
cooperation in consular affairs, sports, social sciences and
economy, consolidating and deepening the friendly cooperation
between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Developing Sino-Mexican economic relations is not only in the
fundamental interests of the two peoples but also of great
importance to world peace and development, says the editorial.
</P>
<P>
Today's world is far from tranquil and the human beings have to
meet various challenges in order to survive and prosper.
</P>
<P>
However, "we hold a firm belief in human progress in the
future. It's an earnest aspiration of world people and the call of
times to maintain world peace and promote common development," it
says.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between countries should be based on equality and
mutual benefit. It has been proved that the world will enjoy
peace, stability and prosperity if all the countries, developing
or developed, build their relations on equality, mutual respect
and mutual benefit, the editorial says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
