<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Hold National Arts Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Eight countries are to
participate in Nigeria's 14th National Festival of Arts and
Culture (Nafest '97) scheduled from December 7 to 13 in the
capital of Abuja, the organizer said here today.
</P>
<P>
The National Council for Arts and Culture said in a statement
that Nafest is expecting delegates from Ghana, Cameroun, Burkina
Faso, Mali, Niger, Cote d'Ivoire, Benin and Iran.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, the seven-day event will feature
traditional wrestling, indigenous pop music, art and craft fair,
dance drama, bazaar, tours and a merit award for art and culture.
</P>
<P>
Nafest, the biggest festival in the country, attracts
participants from all the 36 states across the country. 
</P>
