<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Youths Called to Protect Mt Kilimanjaro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian youths should
protect Mount Kilimanjaro in order to preserve the fauna and
flora which helps bring about ecological balance.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by a representative of the United Nations
Association of Tanzania, William Mbunga, at a press conference in
the city Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said that the United Nations of Youth, Tanzania Branch, a
registered youth initiative, has launched a campaign to arouse
young people's awareness to protect the highest mountain in
Africa, according to today's Daily News.
</P>
<P>
The campaign seeks to arouse young people's awareness of
protecting the 5,895-meter-high mountain which has not been
properly managed.
</P>
<P>
The recent fires in Rombo and Hai districts on the slopes of
the mountain have destroyed more than 10,000 hectares of natural
wetland forest resulting in an enormous loss of fauna and flora.
</P>
<P>
He said the approach to be taken for the campaigning is
through community participation, especially by involving young
people.
</P>
<P>
A dinner will be held today at Nyumba ya Sanaa in Dar es
Salaam to raise money for an expedition to the mountain during
December 10-24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
