<HEADLINE> 6 Palestinians Wounded in Gaza Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Six Palestinians were
wounded today during a clash in the Gaza Strip with Israeli
soldiers who fired live bullets to disperse Palestinian protesters
in a land dispute.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio and state television Channel I quoted
Palestinian sources as reporting that the clash occurred during
a demonstration held by hundreds of Palestinians, who protested
an alleged Israeli plan to set up a military outpost on a
disputed hilltop near Rafaih.
</P>
<P>
The violence erupted when Israeli soldiers tried to clear the
crowd off the area. Some protesters began throwing stones at the
soldiers, who in response used live ammunitions to disperse them.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio said that Israeli army has begun an investigation
into the reported clash.
</P>
<P>
Today's violence highlighted the tense situation at a time
when Israel and the Palestinian National Authority are logged in
a heated dispute over the second phase of the three-stage
Israeli troop redeployments in the West Bank. 
</P>
