<HEADLINE> German Airport Seizes 130 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Customs authorities at the
Duesseldorf airport of Germany announced today that they have
seized 130 kilograms of cocaine on board a passenger plane
arriving from Barcelona, Spain.
</P>
<P>
It was the largest amount of cocaine ever seized at a German
airport, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine, wrapped like Christmas gifts and having a black
market value of about 20 million German marks (11.3 million
U.S. dollars), was found in two metal boxes with the appearance
like diplomatic luggage.
</P>
<P>
A 35-year-old Chad national who arrived on a different flight
from Spain had been arrested in connection with the drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The man carried a service passport of the Republic of Chad but
was not accredited as a diplomat in Germany, customs officials
said. 
</P>
