<HEADLINE> OIC Experts Meeting Ends With Differences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The experts meeting of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) concluded here this
afternoon with some major differences unsolved.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the eighth OIC summit, Iranian Deputy Foreign
Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif told reporters that three issues
unsolved would be referred to the meeting of the OIC foreign
ministers due to open here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Zarif said that the issue of relations of some Islamic
countries with Israel, northern Iraq and the OIC structural
reform remained unsolved due to sharp differences among the OIC
member states.
</P>
<P>
The differences on the issue of relations of Islamic
countries with Israel were serious, he said, but most of the OIC
members including Iran condemned the Israeli hardline policies
and were against the compromise with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The issue of Middle East peace process was the hot topic of
the OIC experts meeting since it opened Tuesday and the Islamic
countries are obviously separated due to the different views on
the issue.
</P>
<P>
Most of the OIC members agreed with the Middle East peace
process while some countries voiced opposition to the process in
the discussion of the OIC political committee.
</P>
<P>
Zarif confirmed the differences among the OIC members over
the Issue of Middle East peace process, saying that it was
natural for the OIC members to have different views.
</P>
<P>
He said that 140 resolutions were adopted during the four-day
discussions in the political, economic and cultural committees.
</P>
<P>
Zarif expressed the hope that the remaining issues would be
solved in the ministerial meeting. 
</P>
