</P>
<P>
-- Financial markets in South Korea soared a day after the
government signed up for the largest IMF bailout ever, but popular
views were mixed -- and the leading candidate for president vowed
to renegotiate the deal if elected.
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. auto makers' sales to Japan slipped into reverse during
the first nine months of this year. The decline is likely to
intensify criticism of Tokyo's trade policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
