<HEADLINE> Army Reduction Exercise Completed in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Acting commander of the
Zimbabwe National Army (ZNA) Major General Amoth Chin'ombe today
said the army had just completed its reduction exercise of
trimming the force from 51,000 to 40,000 members.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''we managed to complete the exercise in the shortest
possible time. We completed it as we entered into a new financial
year and we have to wait and see the results before we start on
new programs for the reduced force.''
</P>
<P>
Chin'ombe was speaking at an occasion to mark the national
tree planting day at Zna's no. one brigade headquarters in
Bulawayo, the country's second largest city.
</P>
<P>
He said the army would continue to participate in programs
which are designed to rehabilitate the depleting of trees and the
destruction of the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
