<HEADLINE> Russian Envoy Meets Hezbollah Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Russia's Middle East
envoy Victor Possevalyuk today met with Hezbollah's
Secretary-General Sheikh Hassan Nasrallah to discuss the progress
of negotiations to swap the remains of dead Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Possevalyuk, who arrived here this morning from Damascus, is
trying to further a measure of progress accomplished by the
Beirut chief delegate of the International Committee of the Red
Cross, JeanJacques Freqier.
</P>
<P>
Israel has accepted the principle of trading living Lebanese
prisoners for the remains of dead Israeli soldiers killed in a
botched seaborne raid in south Lebanon in September.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations have reached the stage of determining the number
of Lebanese prisoners to be freed in exchange for torn limbs of
the Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Hezbollah (Party of God) said in its
statement that the talks between Hasrallah and Possevalyuk
tackled the general situation in the region, especially the
recent escalation of tension in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
It said that they also discussed the situation of Lebanese
prisoners held in Israeli jails and the swap of the remains of
dead Israeli soldiers for Lebanese prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Before meeting Narallah, Possevalyuk also held talks with
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri. 
</P>
</TEXT>
