<HEADLINE> Tourism Year Successful On Southern Chinese Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The "Hainan 1997 China Tourism
Year" has had some good results, according to statistics from
Haikou, the capital of China's island province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released today show a total of 6.15 million tourists
to Hainan in the first ten months of this year, 336,000 of them
overseas, spending 84.61 million US dollars, up 21.6 percent from
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Hainan began making a greater effort to develop tourism earlier
this year, and has held a series of tourism promotions like an
international coconut festival in April, activities in Hong Kong
in June, and a number of trade fairs in other parts of China.
</P>
<P>
The success of the projects has brought greater recognition to
the island, which has become a very attractive place to go for the
people of Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou, according to a recent
poll.  
</P>
</TEXT>
