<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Market Loses 58.02 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) today lost 58.02 points to 3469.08 as
against yesterday's close of 3527.10.
</P>
<P>
The national index downed by 24.33 points to 1504.38 as against
Thursday's close of 1528.71.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 closed lower at 337.79 and the US dollar index at
145.51 from the previous close of 343.03 and 146.40 respectively.
</P>
<P>
After initial rally that took the sensitive index up by 25
points to a day's high of 3552.27, pivotals reacted sharply on
profit taking and tired bull liquidation at the BSE market today
with foreign institutional investors withdrawing while domestic
institutions squaring off positions on the last day of the current
settlement.  
