<HEADLINE> Pharmaceutical Group Annexes Ailing Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A successful
pharmaceutical group in China's Hebei Province has acquired an
ailing pharmaceutical plant in nearby Shanxi Province, after a
careful study done in a short period of time.
</P>
<P>
North China Pharmaceutical Group Corporation Ltd., which was
set up in the 1950s, has established an effective
management system for a modern enterprise and is playing a leading
role in the country's pharmaceutical industry. the Tianyuan
Pharmaceutical Plant (TPT), however, which was also set up in the
1950s, has been running in the red since 1993, and is still 330
million yuan in debt.
</P>
<P>
The group will carry out a series of management and
technological reforms to rescue 500 million yuan in idle capital
at the money-losing plant. After the acquisition, the plant is
expected to have a turnover of 450 million yuan and 33 million
yuan in pre-tax profits next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
