<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji Meets with Publishers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met
today with the authors and publishers of two major works on
engineering at Beijing's Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
The revised "Machine Engineering Handbook" and "Electrical
Machine Engineering Handbook", which were compiled by 2,300 experts
in the 1980s, contain 26 volumes, with 58 million characters, and
are being distributed for the second time. The experts spent 16
years compiling and revising them.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who is a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, is also a
senior engineer.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Song Jian told scholars at today's ceremony
that the two books are milestones in technological history, and a
symbol of the country's progress in the country's science and
technology. 
