<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Releases This Year's Gold Production Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of the
Metallurgical Industry announced today that the country's gold
output will exceed 150 tons this year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Dexue, director of the Ministry's Gold Bureau, said that
by the end of November, China had produced 137.1 tons of gold, up
28 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
This year's output will make China the fifth biggest gold
producer in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
China produced 105 tons of gold in 1995, the first time for the
country's annual gold output to exceed 100 tons. It produced 120
tons of gold in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that there are some problems in the industry with the
declining price of gold, insufficient mineral resources, and a
lack of competitiveness, but that China will attract some foreign
investment to the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
