<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 12:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OIC Summit Good Chance to Settle Difference: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming Islamic Summit in
Tehran will provide a golden chance to settle all differences
among the Islamic countries, said a senior official of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) today.
</P>
<P>
"The Islamic world is in dire need of solidarity in order to
confront challenges facing it," said OIC Assistant General Abdel
Aziz Abu-Ghosh, in an interview with Egyptian Voice of Arabs Radio.
</P>
<P>
The OIC needs to be promoted in order to be able to carry out
this goal, he said.
</P>
<P>
Abu-Ghosh expected the summit to handle many Islamic issues,
including the status of Jerusalem and other occupied Arab
territories as well as the OIC structural readjustment.
</P>
<P>
The 8th OIC Summit to be held on November 9-11 will also
discuss conditions in Afghanistan and Somalia as well as the
dispute between the United Arab Emirates and Iran over the
sovereignty of three islands.
</P>
<P>
It will be attended by heads of state and premiers of 54
OIC member nations.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa will leave here for Tehran
today to attend the ministerial meeting preceding the summit, on
the first visit of a top Egyptian official to Iran since the
Iranian Islamic Revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Arab League Secretary General Esmat Abdel Meguid will also
attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
The Jeddah-based OIC, established in 1970 with a view to
rallying the ranks of the Islamic world, holds a summit meeting
every three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
