<HEADLINE> Electronic Customs System Put into Use in Shenzhen of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- An electronic customs system
was put into use today in Shenzhen, one of China's special
economic zones in Guangdong Province, south China.
</P>
<P>
Because of the Internet and interactive technology, importers
and exporters can submit the bills of entry to the Customs, who
will return results via electronic mail.
</P>
<P>
The system would greatly raise the efficiency of the Customs
service, officials in Shenzhen said.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that 100 clients would log on to the system
each month in the near future. 
</P>
