<HEADLINE> Nagano Olympic Committee Sued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Nagano Olympics Committee
(NOC) was sued for an alleged agreement to provide aerial film of
1998 Winter Olympics opening and closing ceremonies.
</P>
<P>
Japan Business Promotions Propriety Ltd. has filed suit in
Nagano District Court for a compensation totaling 143.1 million
yea (1.1 million U.S. dollars) from the NOC, a company spokesman
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
No furture details were given.
</P>
<P>
The NOC agreed the Australia-based privately-owned company to
take video footage from an airplane at the start and close of the
games in February.
</P>
<P>
The company made a requested bill of the same amount of what
the NOC agreed to pay for the film in the suit which was filed on
November 14, said a Nagano District Court spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The 18th Winter Olympics is to be held from February 7-22 in
Nagano. 
</P>
