<HEADLINE> China Holds Course for State-Owned Enterprise Heads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A month-long course of advanced
studies was launched today for 100 heads of the leading
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongyu, minister in charge of the State Economy and Trade
Commission (SETC), spoke to the group, saying that the heads of
enterprise should improve themselves when building a socialist
market economy.
</P>
<P>
Wang said enterprise reforms are vital to the economic reforms
and that the quality of enterprise leaders is directly tied to the
fate of the plants. He called on them to study modern mangement
techniques and economics, develop a good style of work, be strict
with themselves, and lead their workers to compete in the
marketplace.
</P>
<P>
Today's was the second session of the course, which is
sponsored jointly by the Organization Department of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, the SETC, the Ministry of
Personnel and the Party School of the CPC Central Committee.
