<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Hand Over 111 Bodies to ICRC in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) handed over 111 bodies of government troops to the
International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) in Northern Sri
Lanka today.
</P>
<P>
Information Officer of the Colombo Office of the ICRC Harasha
Gunewadene said that the bodies were handed over to the committee
this morning at Wanni in the north of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC is now in charge of the bodies, which are kept in the
rebel-held territories of Madhu, Northern province.
</P>
<P>
These bodies will be transferred to government troops in
Vavuniya, Northern province, Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Gunewadene said these soldiers were killed in a fierce fighting
Thursday, which lasted from morning till night.
</P>
<P>
The government side so far has shown no intention to hand over
any dead bodies of the LTTE, according to the ICRC official.
</P>
<P>
The Operational Headquarters of the Defense Ministry, when
contacted, said the final figures of casualty were still not
available yet.
</P>
<P>
Early reports said at least 30 soldiers were killed in the
fighting, a major maneuver since the troops launched their final
stage of Operation Jayasikuru (Certain Victory) last month.
</P>
</TEXT>
