<HEADLINE> Japan Provides Co-operative Loans For China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Export-Import Bank of Japan
today provided the Bank of China with 225 million US dollars worth
of co-operative loans.
</P>
<P>
China was previously given 2.351 billion US dollars worth of
the loans by Japan mainly to build 30 major construction projects
during the Eighth Five-Year Plan (1991-1995) period in support of
its infrastructure and raw materials industries.
</P>
<P>
The new loans will be used for key projects like Xiamen's
Haicang Bridge in east China's Fujian province, Shenzhen Airport,
and the Urumqi-Hetian Highway in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
(Uighur) Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Ambassador to China Yochiyasu Sato attended today's
signing ceremony.  
</P>
