<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Arrests 121 Suspected Drug Offenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Central Narcotics Bureau
(CNB) of Singapore arrested a total of 121 suspected drug
offenders from various parts of Singapore, in a continuing effort
to clear the streets of drug pushers and abusers, the CNB said
today.
</P>
<P>
The CNB said that it mounted an islandwide operation under Ops
Dragnet, which started early Thursday morning and ended early
today.
</P>
<P>
Of those arrested, 72 were tested positive for narcotic drugs,
nine for cannabis, two for amphetamine, and two tested positive
for narcotic drugs and cannabis, thus making a total of 85 persons
who were tested positive for controlled drugs.
</P>
<P>
In addition, two sachets and nine straws of heroin, one sachet
of cannabis, four Upjohn tablets and two Erimin tablets were
seized, it said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 85 tested positive, 76 are males and nine are females.
Their ages range between 16 and 51, the CNB said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that 71 of those tested positive for narcotic
drugs abuse had been sent to the Drug Rehabilitation Centers and
those tested positive for amphetamine or cannabis abuse have been
released on bail.
</P>
<P>
The CNB stressed that it will conduct more islandwide
operations to keep up the pressure on illicit drug activities.
</P>
</TEXT>
