<HEADLINE> Pak to Hold Presidential Election on December 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan will hold the
presidential election on December 31, Acting Chief Election
Commissioner Justice Mukhtar Ahmed Junejo announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Nomination papers from the prospective presidential candidates
will be received on December 16, Mukhtar announced the election
schedule two days after the resignation by Farooq Leghari as the
head of state.
</P>
<P>
President Leghari resigned on Tuesday after refusing to sign a
reference against Chief Justice Sajjad Ali Shah who had been
locked in a constitutional confrontation with the government led
by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Senate Chairman Wasim Sajjad has been appointed as the acting
president following Leghari's stepping down.
</P>
<P>
Under Pakistan's Constitution, election for the head of state
is required to be held within 30 days after the vacancy of the
post.
</P>
<P>
The electoral college of the presidential office is formed by
members of the National Assembly, the Senate and four Provincial
Assemblies. The candidate getting a majority of votes in the polls
held on the same day is elevated to the prestigious office.
</P>
<P>
The election by the two houses of Parliament and the four
assemblies for the presidential slot will be held simultaneously
at their respective secretariats.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
