<HEADLINE> Spokesman Comments On DPP Chairman Visit To US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Information
Bureau of the State Council's Taiwan Affairs Office spoke today
about the coming visit of Hsu Hsin-liang, chairman of Taiwan's
Democratic Progressive Party (DPP), to the US.
</P>
<P>
Hsu is scheduled to visit the US and some other countries in
early December, according to Taiwan newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the fact that there is only one China
in the world, that Taiwan is part of China, and that no separation
of China's sovereignty and territorial integrity will be allowed
is common knowledge.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We are firm in our position against 'Taiwan
independence'."
</P>
<P>
Realizing the reunification of China is the common wish of
Chinese on both sides of the Taiwan Straits and an irresistible
historical trend, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that any political force or individual to conduct
activities to split China is against the will of the people and is
bound to fail.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that various parties in Taiwan will go
along with the trend of the times and do something practical to
develop cross-straits relations.  
</P>
