<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberian President Wants Re-definition of ECOMOG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Liberian President Charles
Taylor has called for the re-definition of the west African
peace-keeping force (ECOMOG) in Liberia and Sierra Leone as part
of the conditions for the force's continued stay in his country.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG could stay in Liberia for as long as three years or
more, Taylor said on Thursday at the end of his two-day official
visit to Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"But the functions of ECOMOG in Liberia and Sierra Leone
should be defined and separated," he was quoted by today's press
reports as saying.
</P>
<P>
They are two different cases, Taylor said, but he did not
elaborate.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG was sent to Liberia in 1990 to help end the civil war
there. According to a peace accord, the force will withdraw from
that country from December this year to February next year.
</P>
<P>
The sub-regional force was dispatched to Sierra Leone in the
wake of the May 25 coup that overthrew the legitimate government.
It is enforcing economic sanctions and embargo on that country.
</P>
<P>
The pullout of ECOMOG from Liberia has begun since last
Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, disagreement grew on whether ECOMOG should be
involved in restructuring Liberia's post-war army in line with
the Abuja Peace Accord.
</P>
<P>
Taylor has said earlier it's his constitutional authority to do
the job, thus leading to a rift between him and ECOMOG force
commander Major-General Victor Malu.
</P>
<P>
At Thursday's news briefing, the Liberian leader denied
statements credited to him that he would not allow Liberia to be
used as a base to solved the Sierra Leonean problem.
</P>
<P>
Describing such reports as rumor, Taylor said since Liberia
was a member of the Economic Community of West African States
(ECOWAS), the country will support any ECOWAS plans on Sierra
Leone.
</P>
<P>
Taylor was earlier reported as not allowing ECOMOG to launch
attacks against the military junta in Sierra Leone from Liberia.
</P>
<P>
He also denied reports that Liberia would prefer the United
States to train its army, saying that there would be a departure
from that as a result of the planned African peacekeeping force.
</P>
<P>
As for the allegation that Nigerians are harassed in Liberia
by security agents, Taylor promised to investigate the issue and
take appropriate action against those responsible.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time Taylor visited Nigeria after he was
sworn in as president last August.
</P>
<P>
No communique was released as expected at the end of the
visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Population Reaches 420,300 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The number of residents in Macao
reached 420,300 by the end of September, an increase of 4,400
from last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that during the first nine months this year, Macao
had 3,703 newly-born babies and 984 deaths.
</P>
<P>
While April, May and June seemed to be the least romantic
period to tie the knots in Macao, a total of 1,292 couples got
married in the first three quarters, compared with 1,460 marriages
in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
And Macao may still be an attractive place to live in.
</P>
<P>
The number of foreign nationals allowed to move into Macao was
about the same level as last year, reaching 1,132. But the number
of foreign nationals who had previously lived in Macao but left
between January and September added up to only 473, compared to
780 in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the move-in and departure, Macao had 659 new
residents of foreign nationals.
</P>
<P>
More overseas laborers left Macao in the period, reflecting a
sluggish economy. The number of overseas contract laborers in
Macao declined by 334 to reach 29,566 at the end of September.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a total of 1,526 Chinese nationals were permitted
to emigrate to Macao, and two-thirds of them were women. There
were also 3,938 repatriated illegal immigrants, compared with
5,032 for the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
