<HEADLINE> Macao to Build More Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Macao is to build more schools to
meet the needs for an increasing number of students, local
newspaper Va Kio reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 21 schools have been built in Macao over the past
five years, creating 13,000 vacancies for students. And the
vacancies will increase by 4,000 in the 1997/1998 school year, the
newspaper quoted Luis Viscu, director of the Macao Education and
Youth Department, as saying.
</P>
<P>
These schools, including pre-primary, primary and middle
schools, were the result of joint efforts of the government,
individual institutions, and professionals, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the government will appropriate more land for
building more schools.
</P>
<P>
With more schools, the average number of students for a middle
school class remains at 45 despite the 15-percent increase in the
number of middle school students from the previous school year.
</P>
<P>
Macao now has some 95,000 students in its primary and middle
schools, 6 percent more than in 1996. Most of the students are
attending private schools.  
</P>
</TEXT>
