of the organization committee Thursday evening in Marseille. The
first round, which will open on June 12, 1998, with Brazil against
Scotland at the Stadium of France in Paris, looks appealing. An
explosive group will have the United States, Iran, Germany and
Yugoslavia. The drawing of lot gave France a comfortable group.
</P>
<P>
-- The international conference on Nazi Gold ended Thursday in
London, with the debates having allowed an advancement of the
humanitarian right. A dozen countries, including the United
States, Croatia, Luxembourg, Austria, Brazil, Argentina and
Poland, have agreed to donate to a fund to compensate the
survivors of Nazi genocide in eastern Europe, while the United
States has decided to host a follow-up conference in mid-1998 in
Washington, which will extend the discussion to the arts objects
robbed by Nazis.
</P>
