<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Aquarium to Be Built in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 5 (Xinhua) --Shanghai today began
construction on Asia's largest aquarium.
</P>
<P>
Poly Group Corp. of China and Straco Investment Ltd. of
Singapore jointly invested in the aquarium, which will have a
floor space of 12,000 square meters and a construction area of
more than 28,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
A 120-meter seabed tunnel in the building will feature 30,000
rare, peculiar or giant fishes which fall into 500 species. A
shark exhibition hall also will be built.
</P>
<P>
The project, which costs 55 million U.S. dollars, is scheduled to
be completed by 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
