<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Air Route to Open Between Nanjing, Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The first commercial passenger
plane is expected to fly from Nanjing, capital of east China's
Jiangsu Province, to China's Taiwan Province via Macao on December
29.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement signed here today by Macao Airline,
the China Travel Service of Jiangsu Province and the Nanjing Lukou
International Airport Company, a new air line from Nanjing, via
Macao, to Taipei and Kaohsiung cities in Taiwan will open at the
end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing is also the seventh city in China's interior to
have an air route to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Two round-trip flights are expected to be added next year on
Mondays and Fridays.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Province is one of the inland regions with close
economic and cultural exchanges with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the opening of the air line will play an
important role in boosting exchanges among Jiangsu, Macao and
Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
