<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Generator at Lijiaxia Hydropower Station Goes Online </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The No. 2 generator at the
Lijiaxia Hydropower Station, the biggest of its kind on the upper
reaches of the Yellow River, successfully went online Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The power station, situated on the junction of Jainca County
and Hualong County in northwestern China's Qinghai Province, is
the third of many power stations scheduled for construction on the
upper reaches of the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
Five 400,000-kilowatt turbogenerators will be installed, making
it the country' biggest turbogenerator power station. With a
designed annual generation capacity of 5.9 billion kilowatt/hour
of electricity, the power plant will be jointly financed by the
state, Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region and Shaanxi, Gansu and
Qinghai provinces.
</P>
<P>
Workers with Lijiaxia Bureau of China No. 4 Water Resources and
Hydropower Engineering Administration have overcome many
difficulties to complete the infrastructure and installation of
equipment for the No. 2 generator, so that it can begin operation
as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
During the last three decades, China has built five large- and
medium-size hydropower stations on the upper reaches of the Yellow
River, and installed generators totalling more than three million
kilowatts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
