<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Egyptian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- The trade exchange between Egypt and Turkey is still slight
despite the two countries' trade agreement signed in 1976.
</P>
<P>
The volume of Egyptian exports to Turkey accounted for 3.3
percent of total Egyptian exports while the Egyptian imports from
Turkey made up only 1.2 percent of total Egyptian imports last
year.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Within the framework of the Egyptian efforts to overcome the
negative effects of Luxor terrorist incident, Prime Minister Kamal
el-Ganzouri told the ambassadors of 14 countries accredited to
Egypt that Egypt is cooperating with the international community
to confront terrorist crimes.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa will leave today for
Tehran to attend the two-day meetings of the foreign ministers of
the eighth Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) due Saturday
in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu will meet
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright today in Paris. During
the meeting, Albright is expected to submit some proposals aimed
at accelerating Israeli redeployment in the West Bank. 
</P>
