<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Rising on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued rising
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained another 13.54 points to close at 1713.77 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to 165.86 million units, valued at
384.995 million Singapore dollars (about 240.62 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overtook advances by 207 to 133, while 277
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 7.46 million units. It was followed by
Rekapac which had 7.35 million shares traded. Magnum Corporation
was next with 5.74 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Jurong Shipyard led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1.1
Singapore dollars to end at 9.05 Singapore dollars. Asean Fund and
the DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Foreign increased by 60
cents each to finish at 9.2 U.S. dollars and 16.1 Singapore
dollars respectively. The Singapore Airlines (SIA) Foreign and the
Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign gained 50 cents each to
close at 11.5 and 22.7 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Elec was the biggest loser as it declined by
1.3 dollars to finish at five U.S. dollars. Creative 50 fell by
one dollar to close at 34 Singapore dollars, while Venture was 39
cents lower ending at 4.96 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
