<HEADLINE> Project to Reinforce Yangtze Dike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Completion of the project to
reinforce the dike at Wusongkkou at the mouth of the Yangtze River
marks the removal of hidden perils which could result from
corruption of the embankment.
</P>
<P>
The 1,200-meter dike, designed by the Dutch, was built in 1908
during the Qing Dynasty. The dike has played an indispensible role
throughout this century in controlling shipping activities at the
Yangtze estuary to the East China Sea.
</P>
<P>
However, the dike was in critical need of repair due to damage
resulting from years of silting. Some 30 million yuan has been
spent since April this year to strengthen the dike and protect the
major shipping channel on China's longest river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
