<HEADLINE> Joint Venture to Produce Lubricants in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Fuchs-GHL Lubricants Ltd., a
joint venture between Grease house Ltd. of Bangladesh and Balmer
Lawrie-Fuchs Ltd. of India, will start producing a wide range of
lubricants from next February to cater to local needs, a local
newspaper reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The two companies entered into a technical know-how agreement
in Dhaka Thursday, The Daily Star said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, lubricants for both common household and
industrial use would be gradually produced and introduced in the
Bangladeshi market, and imported base oil will be used as the main
raw material for these types of lubricants.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the high-end environment friendly bio-degradable
lubricants of the world famous "Fuchs" brand will be introduced.
</P>
<P>
"There is a tremendous potential of growth in the lubricant
market of Bangladesh," the newspaper quoted Dr. Manfred Fuchs, the
Fuchs Group chairman, as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We have come to invest in Bangladesh because the Asia-Pacific
part of the world consumes one third of lubricants produced
worldwide," Dr. Fuchs said. "This market is rapidly growing."
</P>
<P>
The total investment of joint venture, which is to be set up in
Bangladesh's second largest city of Chittagong, will be about 40
million taka (about 0.89 million U.S. dollars). The joint venture
will be capable of producing 10,000 tons of lubricants, which is
one fifth of the Bangladesh' annual demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
