<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, December 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- European Union health ministers agreed late on
Thursday that all tobacco advertising has to phase out within six
years in the union.
</P>
<P>
The EU health ministers also agreed on a grace period of two
years for organizers of common events and a grace period of three
years for those of world-level events, such as the Formula One
motor racing and art events, according to diplomatic sources.
(EU-Tobacco Advertising-Ban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japanese Finance Minister Hiroshi Mitsuzuka said today
that the monetary authorities are ready to take action to stop
yen's devaluation against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Admitting that the Japanese economy is now in a tough
situation, Mitsuzuka said the Finance Ministry will take
appropriate measures to stimulate the economy. (Japan-Yen)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- Hungary's Socialist Party
will not cooperate or form alliance with other parties in running
the next general election, Hungarian Prime Minister Horn Gyula
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Instead, the party, which is a ruling partner with the Alliance
of Free Democrats (AFD), will run independently for the National
Assembly as it did in 1990 and 1994.
</P>
<P>
Horn was quoted by the Hungarian News Agency as saying that the
situation in Hungary has never been so good. (Hungary-Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A Foreign Ministry spokesman said today that the
decision to reduce ground and naval forces in northwest Russia,
announced by President Boris Yeltsin in Sweden, is part of
Russia's military reform,
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the suggestion would further the
implementation of the Treaty on Conventional Armed Forces in
Europe.
</P>
<P>
He asked the Western countries to clearly define their
army building plans in accordance with current security situation
in Europe. (Russia-Military)
</P>
<P>
