</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) today
approved South Korea's request for a three-year stand-by credit
equivalent to about 21 billion U.S. dollars in support of the
government's economic and financial program.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, about 5.56 billion dollars is available
immediately while about 3.58 billion dollars will be available on
December 18 following the first review under the program.
(IMF-S.Korea-Credit)
</P>
<P>
