<P>
BELGRADE -- French and German foreign ministers today called
for peacekeepers to stay in Bosnia after their current mandate
expires by the end of June next year.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine and his German
counterpart Klaus Kinkel said it's essential to maintain the
presence of the NATO-led multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR)
as only a small part of the so-called Dayton accord to bring peace
back to Bosnia has been implemented up to
now.(BC-Bosnia-France-Germany) 
