<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Enterprises Merge in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Haihua Group of Weifang,
Shandong Province, merged 17 enterprises in October to establish a
large oceanic chemical company with assets hitting eight billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The merger will enhance the competitive edge of Haihua, pushing
the number of best-selling products in the oceanic chemical
industrial sector from four to eight, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
The case in Haihua is only one of the many examples of
cross-regional and cross-industry association of enterprises in
Shandong, a province in east China. Many other enterprises have
lowered costs through mergers, associations, purchase and
shareholding.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 1,000 enterprise groups in Shandong have
assets of 500 million yuan or more each, and two dozens of them
have assets around five billion yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Capital overhaul in Qingdao, a port city in Shandong, have
produced nine groups entering China's top 500 industrial
enterprises list.
</P>
<P>
Xihu Electronics Group, which became a share-holding company of
the Haier Group this September, recorded an increase in sales
revenue of 80 percent and profits of 47.8 percent over the same
period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
