<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Senate Urged to Ratify Nuclear Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today asked the Senate to ratify an agreement on the application
of safeguards on nuclear energy use in connection with the treaty
on the non-proliferation of nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
The protocol to the agreement was signed by the Philippines and
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) in Vienna, Austria,
in September 1997, according to a press release from the
Presidential Press Office.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Senate President Ernesto Maceda, Ramos said he
hoped the agreement would be quickly passed to address the need
for safeguards on nuclear energy use so as not to hamper the
economic and technological development of the Philippines or
international cooperation in peaceful use of nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for safeguards that would respect the
health, safety, physical protection and other security provisions
to protect the rights of individuals.
</P>
<P>
Under the Philippine Constitution, no treaty can take effect
unless it is ratified by the Senate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
