<HEADLINE> Tianjin to Relocate Polluting Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, north China's largest
port city, plans to relocate 80 polluting enterprises as part of
an effort improve the urban environment, according to the
Beijing-based "China Environmental News".
</P>
<P>
The city's industrial layout lags behind economic development,
with many industrial enterprises sitting in bustling downtown or
residential areas creating increasingly serious pollution harmful
to local residents.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises scheduled for relocation operate facilities
covering 1.51 million square meters. The municipal government is
seeking investments to finance the relocation projects. Various
projects have been initiated and a number of others are currently
drafting plans to attract investments from home and abroad. 
</P>
