<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Chinese City Has Files on Bridges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The 166 bridges crisscrossing
this capital of eastern China's Zhejiang Province now have their
own "health files."
</P>
<P>
The files contain 15 items of information such as the bridges'
routes, structure, maintenance schedule, building material and
photographs.
</P>
<P>
To better protect local bridges, the tourist city of Hangzhou
established bridge files in 1989, with half covering ancient
bridges such as Duanqiao Bridge, the oldest in the city built in
the Tang Dynasty (618-907).
</P>
<P>
According to these files, regular examinations such as shaking
tests are performed monthly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
