<HEADLINE> Fierce Fighting Kills 50 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Intense fighting between
government troops and rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) killed more than 30 troops and at least 26 rebel
guerrillas in the north Thursday, a local radio station reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The Yes FM Radio Station said the troops suffered heavy loss of
lives when they tried to capture a rebel base in the Northern
jungles.
</P>
<P>
The confrontation began in the morning and lasted late into the
night.
</P>
<P>
Some soldiers were missing in action. The injured were admitted
to hospitals in Colombo and Anuradhapura, capital of the Northern
Central Province.
</P>
<P>
The troops are engaged in the final phase of Operation
Jayasikuru (Certain Victory) to open a land route running to the
north through rebel-controlled territories.
</P>
<P>
The government is keen to clear the highway to ensure a supply
route to the north both for military supplies and essentials for
the civilians.
</P>
<P>
For a long time supplies have been transported by air and sea,
too costly to the government.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting against the government for
a separate state in the north and east of the country since 1983.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
