<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Environmental Protection Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The China Intl. Environmental
Protection Exhibition opened today in the Beijing Exhibition
Center.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the exhibition, jointly sponsored by the State
Bureau of Environmental Protection (SBEP) and the Chinese
Association of Environmental Protection Industry, is to promote
the development of China's environmental industry by expanding
exchanges and cooperation with other countries.
</P>
<P>
SBEP Director Xie Zhenhua said that China will persist in its
sustainable development strategy, and allocates a total of 450
billion yuan (56 billion US dollars) for pollution control during
the 1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
"China has a vast potential market for environmental protection
equipment and technology, " said Xie, who also expressed hope that
more overseas businessmen will enter the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition will feature technology and equipment
related to pollution control, clean production, recycling
resources, ecological protection and environmental monitoring.
</P>
<P>
More than 280 manufacturers from China's provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions, as well as representatives
from a number of ministries, are attending the exhibition which
has also attracted 54 companies from 14 countries, including the
United States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The China-Europe Environmental Symposium being held in
conjunction with the exhibition will feature 11 lectures and 14
technology fairs.
</P>
<P>
Sources note that the exhibition will be held once every two
years.
</P>
<P>
Small firms account for some 80 percent of 7,500 companies in
China's environmental protection industry which has an annual
output of some 30 billion yuan (3.7 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
