<HEADLINE> UNDP Funds Ma'anshan Garbage Disposal Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A garbage disposal center, funded
by the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), is under
construction in Ma'anshan, a traditional industrial base with a
poor urban environment in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The center, covering an area of eight hectares, will not only
dispose of rubbish, but will also generate methane gas, according
to the designer. Methane gas will be piped to 20,000 households in
the surrounding area.
</P>
<P>
The center will also include sewage treatment facilities and a
methane power plant.
</P>
<P>
The designer noted that the center will serve as a good example
of environmental protection, and added that using methane gas
produced from garbage will help reduce emissions of greenhouse
gases. 
</P>
