<HEADLINE> Lebanese Shiite Leader Survives Assassination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Leader of Lebanese Higher
Islamic Shiite Council Sheikh Mohammed Shamseddine Thursday night
survived an assassination when he was praying inside the Imam Ali
mosque here, local newspaper the Daily Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
The council's press attache Mohammed Amin told the paper that
two gunmen with pistols with silencers entered the mosque's
courtyard and fired several shots after one of the cleric's
bodyguards, Bassem Shamseddine, noticed activity in nearby trees.
</P>
<P>
"The bodyguard was slightly wounded in the forehead but the
gunmen escaped and, the Sheikh was quickly escorted out of the
mosque," Amin said.
</P>
<P>
Amin refused to speculate on the motives behind the attack,
saying the council wouldn't issue a statement.
</P>
<P>
"Our responsibility is to explain the details of the incident
but we will not comment further," he said.
</P>
<P>
State prosecutor Adnan Addoum said that he had immediately
dispatched Beirut public prosecutor Abdullah Bitar and a team
from the central criminal evidence department to investigate the
incident.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese President Elias Hrawi and a host of officials
later contacted Shamseddine to express their relief that he had
been unharmed in the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
