<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Cambodian Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Community Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, met today with a delegation from
the Cambodian People's Party (CPP).
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the secretariat of the CPC central
Committee, warmly welcomed the delegation led by Say Chhum, a
permanent member of the Political Bureau of the CPP Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Hu noted the long friendship between China and Cambodia, and
said the CPC hopes to increase friendly contacts with CPP on the
basis of the four principles of party-to-party relations and to
promote healthy and stable bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Say Chhum expressed the CPP's willingness to further develop
friendly cooperative ties between the two countries and the two
parties.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian delegation, which arrived in Beijing on Monday,
is visiting China at the invitation of the CPC.  
</P>
