<HEADLINE> China's Largest Sugar Production Group Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- China's largest sugar
production group has recently been established in Nanning, capital
city of south China's Guangxi Zhuang Automonous Region, based on
24 sugar refineries of this region.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the Nanning Prefecture Sugar Group Co.Ltd
is expected to promote the development of sugar industry in
Nanning Prefecture, one of the most important sectors in its
economic growth, a local official said.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture, the largest sugar production base in Guangxi,
has dedicated 150,000 ha. to the production of sugar cane. The
group's 24 sugar refineries have a total daily pressing capacity
of 65,000 tons of sugar.
</P>
<P>
The newly established sugar production group will produce
850,000 tons of sugar annually, or approximately 11 percent of the
nation's total sugar output.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture plans to produce more than 10 million tons of
sugar cane and press 1.1 million tons of sugar annually by the
turn of the century, corporate sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sugar pressing industry, the prefecture's leading economic
sector, contributes 27 percent of the local industrial output
value and 43 percent of total revenues.  
</P>
</TEXT>
