<HEADLINE> Nanjing Publishes Book on Maritime History and Culture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, capital of east
China's Jiangsu Province, has published an academic work on the
city's ancient culture -- "Maritime Sovereignty and Cultural
History".
</P>
<P>
The work covers the marine sovereignty and cultural history of
Nanjing, the capital of a number of dynasties over a 1,500 year
period in ancient China.
</P>
<P>
The 700,000-word book is divided into two section: Maritime
History, and Relics and Archeology. The two sections contain the
results of detailed historical research on Zheng He, an ancient
master navigator of the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644).
</P>
<P>
The work also includes abundant research documents concerning
the development of China's maritime sovereignty in ancient
times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
