<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- An irrigation project partially
funded with World Bank loans has been completed in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Total investments in the project, constructed over the past
eight years, stood at 1.3 billion yuan, including World Bank loans
of 115.4 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Implementation of the project, which will benefit 28 counties
and districts, has helped improve the quality of 438,000 ha of
previously low-yield farmland and increase grain output by 358,200
tons.
</P>
<P>
