<HEADLINE> Philippine Rebels Release Two Captives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The armed wing of the Philippine
National Democratic Front (NDF) today released two captives and
turned them over to representatives of the International Committee
of the Red Cross (ICRC) in an undisclosed place in the northern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Police said an NDF spokesman presided over the release of
Police Captain Rene Francisco and Army Sergeant Joaquin Melad, who
were captured by the rebels last month in an attack on Eastern
Rodriquez Town, Rizal Province, the northern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Police said the ICRC representatives turned over the two
captives to government officials led by House Speaker Jose de
Venecia, who went up to the mountainous village of Santa Ines,
Quezon, southeast of Manila, to recover them.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia, who was accompanied by the captives' families and
reporters, thanked the rebels for the safe release of their
prisoners. 
</P>
