<HEADLINE> China-Peru Joint Economic Committee Meets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Peruvian economic and
trade officials met here today to explore new avenues for
expanding bilateral economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Both the Chinese and Peruvian governments sent their senior
representatives to the session, the second of the kind, of the
China-Peru Economic and Trade Mixed Committee.
</P>
<P>
Leading the Chinese delegation was Yang Wensheng, assistant to
China's Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation minister.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and Peruvian officials agreed that the two countries
share a lot common interests and have bright prospectives for
furthering economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the current meeting was to review the existing
bilateral trade and economic ties, and study the possibilities of
furthering the cause, they said.
</P>
<P>
Peru's exports to China equal the combined volume of exports to
its four major South American partners, said Peruvian officials.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between the two countries has made rapid progress
after the first session of the China-Peru Economic and Trade Mixed
Committee in 1992, Chinese officials said.
</P>
<P>
Peru now is China's forth largest trade partner in Latin
America. 
</P>
