<HEADLINE> Famous Protestant Church Burnt Down in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A famous wooden Protestant
church in Miskole, the second largest city of Hungary, was burnt
down this morning, newspapers reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire occurred at the small hours this morning. Though the
fire was put out after several hours, the church along with all
its internal facilities were burnt down, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary police investigation suspected arson, saying that
anyone who gives useful clues for the case will receive an award
of 500,000 forint (about 2,500 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The church, built in 1938, is one of the most famous buildings
in Miskole. It will cost an estimated 6 to 8 million forint (about
30,000 to 40,000 dollars) to rebuild. 
</P>
</TEXT>
