<HEADLINE> Hungarian Socialists to Independently Run General Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's Socialist Party
will not cooperate or form alliance with other parties in running
the next general election, Hungarian Prime Minister Horn Gyula
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Instead, the party, which is a ruling partner with the Alliance
of Free Democrats (AFD), will run independently for the National
Assembly as it did in 1990 and 1994.
</P>
<P>
Horn was quoted by the Hungarian News Agency as saying that the
situation in Hungary has never been so good.
</P>
<P>
But he said it is still possible that the Socialist party will
have to jointly run the country with AFD after the next election.
</P>
<P>
He said what matters most in Socialist Party's choice of a
ruling parter is the common ground with its potential partners,
not the differences in their election platforms.
</P>
</TEXT>
