<HEADLINE> Guangdong Posts Record Grain Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
province has had yet another record grain output in 1997, thereby
fulfilling production targets for the Ninth Five Year Plan
(1996-2000) three years ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
Despite frequent natural disasters throughout the year, the
province managed to increase its grain output by 600,000 tons to
19.48 million tons. Guangdong has recorded four successive bumper
havests.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government, which has consistently placed
priority on the grain sector, allocated five billion yuan late
last year to improve water conservation facilities and upgrade
low-yield farmland.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it established some 50 grain production bases and
designated 14 counties as commodity grain suppliers.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of intensive technological applications has
also been a major factor contributing to good harvests, according
to local officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
