<HEADLINE> American Figure Skater Wins Men's Title At Junior Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Derrick Delmore of the United
States won the men's title on Thursday night at the World Junior
Figure Skating Championships held at Saint John, Canada.
</P>
<P>
Delmore edged out Sergei Davydov of Russia in the free skate
competition with Li Yunfei of China finishing third.
</P>
<P>
Italians Federica Faiella and Luciano Milo went top in the
original dance to finish first in the ice dancing event.
</P>
<P>
Americans Jessica Joseph and Charles Butler placed second after
coming in second in the original dance.
</P>
<P>
Oksana Potdykova and Denis Petukhov of Russia took the third
slot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
