<HEADLINE> Romania's Reform Achieves Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister
Victor Ciorbea said today that the economic adjustment in his
country has achieved initial success.
</P>
<P>
Summing up his one-year work at the joint meeting of the Senate
and Chamber of Deputies, Ciorbea said the exchange rate between
the Romanian currency, the leu, and hard currencies has been
stable.
</P>
<P>
Foreign reserves have increased from 700 million U.S. dollars
earlier this year to 2.6 billion dollars now, the highest since
World War II, and foreign investment amounted to more than one
billion dollars in one year, as much as the total in the previous
four years.
</P>
<P>
On the rise of inflation, he said it was a temporary situation.
</P>
<P>
The country had a large grain harvest this year, but industrial
production dropped, a problem which all countries in the
transition period have faced.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian government would continue its economic reform,
strictly control inflation and crack down on tax evasion to
guarantee the stability of the national economy, Ciorbea stressed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Romanian parliament today approved Ciorbea's
cabinet reshuffle plan. 
</P>
