another step to assist judicial reform in Latin America and the
Caribbean by approving a 22.5 million U.S. dollar loan for Peru.
</P>
<P>
The Judicial Reform project is designed to modernize the
administrative structure and operation of the judiciary, develop a
merit-based and transparent judicial career system while improving
its performance.
</P>
<P>
