of the Judicial System, which include the Judiciary, the Judiciary
Training Academy, the Judicial Council and the newly created
Ombudsman's Office.
</P>
<P>
Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs) will have the opportunity
to participate in the project through a demand-driven access fund
which will finance civil community initiatives to monitor the
judicial reform process.
</P>
<P>
The Inter-American Development Bank (IDB), which is
collaborating with the World Bank on judicial reform in Peru, has
provided a 1.4 million dollars technical assistance grant and is
preparing another project for the sector. 
