<HEADLINE> Hainan Accelerates Expressway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a 98-km
expressway linking Yangpu and Basuo on the midwestern coast of
Hainan Island in south China commenced recently.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will cost 900 million yuan and is scheduled for
completion by 1998. The new road will link Danzhou City, Baisha
County, Changjiang County and Dongfang City in the western part of
the island province.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Deputy Governor Wang Xiaofeng said the project
symbolizes the accelerated construction of an expressway ringing
the island.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that Hainan will work hard to complete construction
of the expressway system prior to the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Hainan has proceeded in line with local conditions and has
invested heavily in expressway construction over the past few
years.
</P>
<P>
The 268-km expressway in eastern Hainan opened to traffic in
1995. Expansion of the northern section of the expressway, from
Haikou, the provincial capital on the northern end of the island,
to Qionghai, a city on mideastern coast, commenced in late 1996
and is scheduled for completion next March. Expansion of the
southern section, from Qionghai to Lingshui, will begin within the
year.
</P>
<P>
The expressway in the western part of the island will stretch a
total of 366 kilometers. The upper northern section from Haikou to
Yangpu opened in March this year. Construction of the southwestern
section, from Jiusuo to Sanya, a seaside resort on the southern
tip of Hainan Island, commenced in January this year and will be
completed in March 1998.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary work for construction of the remaining 90 km
section of the western expressway from Basuo to Jiusuo is
proceeding smoothly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
