<HEADLINE> Anhui Attracts Overseas Investment for Pollution Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
has granted a 140 million US dollars loan for pollution control
projects in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used for six pollution control projects --
the Chaohu Lake Sewage Treatment Plant and a sewage treatment
plant in the provincial capital of Hefei, as well as the Anhui
Chaohu Lake Cement Company Ltd., Hefei Chemical Fertilizer Plant,
Hefei Chemical Plant and Hefei Iron and Steel Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The projects will be carried out at a total cost of 2.8 billion
yuan (350 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Related projects will help to reduce the annual volume of
wastewater discharged into the Chaohu Lake, one of China's five
largest freshwater lakes, by 35.69 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
