<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Japanese newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- A key advisory panel of the Japanese government released a
final report Thursday urging the government to relax legal and
administrative regulation for 22 business and social sectors in a
bid to spur competition.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- Fuji Bank-led Fuyo group decided Thursday to support the
troubled Yasuda Trust and Banking.
</P>
<P>
Yomiuri, Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- Japan's Central Labor Standards Council unveiled Thursday a
final report on amendments to the labor law, calling for
increasing the types of jobs in which some employees are paid
fixed wages despite unfixed working hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
