<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, December 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- The British and United States governments warned the
Iraqi government on Thursday they would not rule out military
option if Baghdad tried to restrict United Nations arms
inspections.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference after talks with U.S.
Defense Secretary William Cohen, British Defense Secretary George
Robertson said, "The clear message for this country and indeed for
the whole world is that this crisis is not over."
</P>
<P>
Robertson made the statement after the Iraqi government
restricted U.N. arms inspectors from visiting certain presidential
palaces and other facilities in Iraq. (UK-US-Iraq)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The three-day international conference on Nazi gold
ended in London on Thursday afternoon with its Chairman Lord
Mackay calling it "a memorable and most stimulating conference."
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the final press conference, Lord Mackay said that
some 240 delegates from 41 countries and six non-government
organizations have "made extremely useful discussion" on the
origins and fate of the Nazi gold. (UK-Conference-Nazi Gold )
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia completed the destruction of 20 sea-launched
ballistic missiles of its Northern fleet Thursday in the framework
of the Strategic Offensive Arms Reduction Treaty (START-1),
according to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Twelve out of these missiles were destroyed Wednesday. Three
missiles were launched from a strategic nuclear submarine of the
Typhoon type in the Barents Sea and were destroyed by 10:30 Moscow
time Thursday, while five more missiles were destroyed later in
the day, the National Nuclear Risk Reduction Center was quoted as
saying. (Russia-Missiles-Elimination)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Two crew members were killed in the crash of a
U.S. AH-64 Apache attack helicopter in Texas Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two-seat aircraft went down at around 10:20 a.m. CST (16:20
GMT) during a routine training flight in a remote area of central
Texas, the United Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft was attached to the 4th Infantry Division, 1st
Battalion, 4th Aviation.
</P>
<P>
The Army has dispatched investigators to the scene to
investigate the cause of the accident. (US-Helicopter-Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- China reiterated Thursday that the
enlargement of the U.N. Security Council should follow the
principle of equitable geographical distribution and ensure a
proper balance between the developing and developed nations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to the United Nations Qin Huasun told the
52nd Session of U.N. General Assembly that the international
community needs to be vigilant against the proposal for admitting
some countries into the Security Council in a "quick fix" manner
"through the backdoor". (China-UN-Security Council Reform)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has talked with
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright on the Middle East peace
process before she meets with Israeli and Palestinian leaders in
Europe on the weekend, The White House said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Mike McCurry told reporters that Clinton
and Albright agreed that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat should "focus intently on the
immediate issues" that the United States had put
forward. (US-Mideast-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The United States welcomed
Russia's offer to reduce military forces on its borders with the
Baltic states, a State Department spokesman announced today.
</P>
<P>
"We haven't had an opportunity to study the proposals but we've
had a cursory look at them," said State Department spokesman James
Rubin when referring to a statement by Russian President Boris
Yeltsin during a current visit to Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that Russia would unilaterally cut its ground and
naval forces by 40 percent in just over a year while his aides
said this would apply to northern Russia bordering the Baltic
states. (US-Russia-Baltics) 
</P>
</TEXT>
