<HEADLINE> Holmes To Meet Challenger Vaden in Title Bout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 4 (Xinhua) -- World Boxing Council (WBC)
middleweight champion Keith Holmes will finally face the challenge
from the former IBF junior welterweight champion Paul Vaden at the
Pompano Beach Amphitheater to make just his second title defense
on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Holmes' fight calendar in 1997 has been full of open dates and
cancellations although he made a promise to be a frequent defender
after he won the WBC middleweight title over Quincy Taylor in
March, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Holmes, with a 29-1 record and 19 knockouts, defended his title
for the first time by stopping Richie Woodhall in 12 rounds in
October, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Two scheduled defenses against Vaden have been postponed,
extending Holmes's ring inactivity to 13 months.
</P>
<P>
Vaden, with a record of 27-1 and 14 knockouts, had a four-month
reign as junior-welterweight champion in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
