<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0268 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwestern China Region Plans Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A large trade fair will be
held in September of 1998 to mark the 40th anniversary of the
founding of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The regional bureau of foreign trade and economic cooperation
planned the event to promote the opening-up of Ningxia and,
eventually, advancing development of the region's foreign trade
and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The fair will be jointly held by the bureau, the regional
planning and economic commissions and China Council for Promotion
of International Trade Ningxia Branch.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 business people from China and overseas will be
invited to attend the fair during which commodity exhibitions and
seminars will also be held.
</P>
<P>
The regional government will also publish a list of projects
for economic cooperation which will involve development of
agricultural resources, construction of infrastructure for energy
and transportation, and transfer of scientific and technological
achievements.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region was founded in October of 1958
and has a population of five million, one-third of whom are Hui
Moslems.
</P>
<P>
Great changes have taken place in the region since it was
established. So far, overseas business people from 26 countries
and regions have invested in this land-locked area and have
started more than 400 overseas-backed businesses there involving a
total investment of 280 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The region did one billion U.S. dollars in imports and exports
in 1996, with exports accounting for 11.8 percent of the region's
gross domestic product. 
</P>
</TEXT>
