<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Personnel Training Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Pasona Group from Japan
and the Shanghai Foreign Service Co. Ltd. plan to jointly
establish a personnel training center.
</P>
<P>
The center will provide training enabling laid off workers from
state-owned enterprises find new employment, including jobs with
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Pasona Group will provide 10 million yen in funding for the
center which will also train white-collar workers for joint
ventures.
</P>
<P>
The Pasona Group is one of the world's top 10 personnel
training organizations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
