<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Cup Draw Held in Marselle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The defending champions Brazil
will kick off the 1998 World Cup finals against Scotland,
according to the World Cup draw mad at Marselle late on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony, presided by the General Secretary of FIFA, Josegh
Blatter, seperated the 32 qualifiers in eight groups.
</P>
<P>
The 1994 World Cup losing finalists Italy will play their first
group match at the 1998 World Cup finals against Chile.
</P>
<P>
Hosts France will encounter South Africa in a Group C match in
Marselle on June 12, while the first-time qulifiers Japan and
Jamaica were grouped in Group H together with Argentina and
Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The representatives of 32 qualifying nations and 10 host cities
of France presented the Ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Before the ceremony, the European all-star team played an
exhibition match against the Rest of the World team. The match
ended 5-2 in favor of the Rest of the World which was led by
superstar Ronaldo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
