<HEADLINE> Thierry Roussel Ordered to Appear Before Greek Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Thierry Roussel, father of
12-year-old Onassis heiress Athina, has been ordered to stand
trial before an Athens criminal court on charges of perjury,
slander and defamation against the board of the Alexander S.
Onassis Public Benefit foundation.
</P>
<P>
The indictment, which was issued by an Athens appeal court on
November 28, said that there was substantial evidence against
Roussel to be referred for trial by a court of misdemeanors for
"perjury, slander and defamation" in connection with false
allegations of mismanagement of the foundation's assets by its
four Greek board members, including the foundation's President,
Stelio Papadimitriou, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
No dates have been set for the hearings.
</P>
<P>
Papadimitriou said today that he had no personal dispute with
Roussel, but the latter had insulted what was most sacred for the
board.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that Roussel would come to Greece and appear before
the court.
</P>
<P>
The foundation was founded by Aristotle Onassis shortly after
his death in 1975. Roussel and the four other trustee, including
Papadimitriou, are responsible for managing Athina's 3 billion
fortune until she reaches adulthood.
</P>
<P>
A bitter legal battle between Roussel and the four other
trustees began after Roussel claimed last month that there was a
plot to kidnap Athina.
</P>
<P>
The foundation insists that there was no such plot, but rather
a check on Roussel's arrangements for Athina's security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
