following the recent controversial designation of 1,480 farms by
the government under the 1992 land acquisition act.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe urged delegates to the conference to deliberate on the
land issue as openly as possible.
</P>
<P>
"In this respect, all party members here should discuss this
issue frankly and in detail, focusing properly on how the land to
be acquired should be distributed and managed without any
decrease in production," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "increased production and productivity in
agriculture should be the watchword."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, on Thursday afternoon a full report of the National
Land Acquisition Committee, which was charged by ZANU (PF)
National Chairman Joseph Msika, was submitted to the politburo
meeting and later to the central committee meeting for adoption
in readiness for presentation to the national party conference on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe will present the central committee report to the
national party conference on Friday which he said would focus on
the land question, the indigenization of the economy, state
assistance to former freedom fighters, the HIV/AIDS pandemic, the
state of the party and gender issues. 
