<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia's Northern Fleet Eliminates 20 Missiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Russia completed the destruction
of 20 sea-launched ballistic missiles of its Northern fleet today
in the framework of the Strategic Offensive Arms Reduction Treaty
(START-1), according to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Twelve out of these missiles were destroyed Wednesday. Three
missiles were launched from a strategic nuclear submarine of the
Typhoon type in the Barents Sea and were destroyed by 10:30 Moscow
time today, while five more missiles were destroyed later in the
day, the National Nuclear Risk Reduction Center was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Seven U.S. military inspectors monitored the destruction of
missiles.
</P>
<P>
Russian military experts believe that the proposed method of
utilization is the cheapest and not hazardous either for the World
ocean or for the earth's atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the destroyed RSM-52 missiles (SS-20
missiles under the foreign classification) were three-stage
solid-fuel missiles of the sixth generation with 10 independently
targeted warheads. Their average range is over 8,000 kilometers,
the weight at the launching is 50 tons.
</P>
<P>
It said that under the START-1 treaty, which was signed in 1991
and came into effect on December 1994, Russia eliminated more than
800 launchers of intercontinental ballistic missiles and
sea-launched ballistic missiles, some 2,000 missiles, 20 nuclear
submarines and more than 50 heavy bombers.
</P>
<P>
The United States destroyed over 600 launchers of
intercontinental ballistic missiles, sea-launched ballistic
missiles, some 450 missiles, 22 nuclear submarines and more than
270 heavy bombers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Killed by Mysterious Animal in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The northeastern region of
Bari in Somalia is facing fatalities from a mysterious animal at
a time when the southern regions of the country are suffering
from natural disasters caused by heavy rains and floods.
</P>
<P>
In the last 15 days, six people have died and eight others
were wounded after they were attacked and eaten by the unknown
animal in Bari region.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from the VHF radios, the animal, small
and skinny with white tail attacked the people in the less
populated areas outside the towns and villages.
</P>
<P>
On Monday and Tuesday this week, the animal has eaten two
people in the town of Qardo, nearly 150 km south of the regional
capital, Bossaso.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the animal about the size of a wolf jumped on
the torso of the person and sucked the blood and then ate the
flesh with all the bones.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the animal has the ability to
finish the whole body of the person within minutes before anyone
comes for his/her help.
</P>
<P>
The pieces of three human being flesh believably eaten by
these animals were also found in two other districts, Iskushban
and Hurdia a week ago.
</P>
<P>
The last known victim was a woman wounded by the animal
locally given the name of 'Hintifaa' who was brought to a
hospital in Bossaso yesterday after gunmen rushed out for her
rescue. The gunmen have reportedly shot and killed the animal.
The body of the animal was also dragged to Bossaso where the
people watched it for several hours before setting it on fire.
</P>
<P>
Eight more animals of this kind were also killed after
numerous gunmen went out to hunt for them in the country.
</P>
<P>
The people of the region believe that these animals have
originally crossed from the border with Ethiopia into Somalia.
The eyewitnesses also said the animals usually wait for the
people near the garbage collection sites where they also eat the
thrown out animal bones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
