<HEADLINE> Iraqi FM Arrives in Iran for OIC Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Foreign Minister
Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf arrived here this afternoon to attend
the ministerial meeting of the Organization of Islamic Conference
(OIC) due to open Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for an Iraqi foreign minister to visit
Iran after the eight-year bloody war between the two rival
neighbors between 1980 and 1988, the Iranian official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
According to IRNA, al-Sahhaf and his six-member delegation
entered Iran's land through the border point of Khosravi in
Iran's western province of Kermanshah this morning.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sahhaf was received at Tehran's international airport by
his Iranian counterpart Kamal Kharrazi, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
While in Kermanshah, IRNA said, the Iraqi foreign minister
confirmed that Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan would
lead a high-ranking delegation to the eighth OIC summit to be
held here on December 9-11.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Tehran summit would provide a good
opportunity for Muslim states to raise problems facing the
Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the heads of the Islamic states should discuss
problems in the Muslim world and take initiatives to further
broaden economic and political cooperation among them and remove
the present hindrance.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sahhaf recommended the OIC summit to concentrate on topics
such as military presence of world powers in the region and
economic sanctions imposed on Muslim nations, including Iran,
Iraq, Libya and Sudan. 
</P>
