<HEADLINE> Tunisia, France Sign Loan Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia and France signed today
an agreement whereby the French Development Fund would provide a
loan of 23.8 million Tunisian dinars (21.6 million U.S. dollars)
to the Tunisian government, Tunisian news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Tunisian Minister of International
Cooperation and Investment Mohamed Channouchi and the fund's
director Francois Ghadat, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be earmarked for financing the agricultural
development program in north and north-west Tunisia, which is
part of the country's ninth development plan (1997-2001).
</P>
<P>
The program aims to promote the living conditions of the
inhabitants of those areas, improving agricultural output and
cattle breeding, and preservation of lands.
</P>
<P>
The loan is within the framework of the partnership agreement
signed by the two countries during last September's visit to
France by Tunisian President Zine Al-Abidine Ben Ali. 
