<HEADLINE> S. Africa Expects Dry Summer: Weather Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The El Nino weather
phenomenon is still in a position to cause dry, scorching weather
in Southern Africa in the next few months, a local weather expert
has predicted.
</P>
<P>
The dry weather is expected despite good rain in South Africa
recently. Up to 120 millimeters of rain had fallen in a number of
planting areas, and more rain is expected in the next two weeks
in spite of El Nino, said weather expert Willem Landman.
</P>
<P>
However, Landman warned that there was no reason to believe
the El Nino weather pattern had weakened.
</P>
<P>
He said the effects of El Nino should begin to be felt later
this month.
</P>
<P>
El Nino is a warming of the South Pacific, which causes
adverse weather conditions in many parts of the world, including
drought and torrential rains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
