<HEADLINE> IDB Assists Municipal Development in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 60
million U.S. dollar loan to Colombia to back the consolidation and
expansion of the municipal credit market.
</P>
<P>
The resources will finance investments as well as technical
assistance for improvement in the areas such as water and
sewerage, transportation, environmental protection, parks solid
waste management, housing in low-income neighborhoods, telephone
systems and educational facilities.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program, Colombia's second municipal
development project, is some 200 million dollars. In addition to
the IDB loan, which is for a 20-year term, local counterpart will
fund total 80 million dollars. The World Bank is expected to
provide 60 million dollars in financing.
</P>
<P>
Previous IDB loans to this country this year totaled 64.5
million dollars, in support of investments in areas of land
titling, fiscal reform, energy and road construction. The Bank
also approved this year a 31.5 million dollar risk guarantee for a
private sector project in Colombia, the first such guarantee by
the IDB. 
</P>
