<HEADLINE> S. African Rape Cases Still Top World's List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 4 (Xinhua) -- South Africa tops the
world's list of reported rapes, while occupying fourth position
for murder, according to a latest survey by the International
Criminal Police Organization, Interpol.
</P>
<P>
The Paris-based organization said the incidence of rape
appears to be on the increase, which was attributed by Interpol
to renewed emphasis on crimes against children and women as a
South African national priority.
</P>
<P>
However, South Africa's Ministry of Safety and Security said
earlier that the crime wave in the country was slowly turning.
</P>
<P>
The ministry's quarterly crime report shows a decrease in
arson, murder and robbery in South Africa, but it gives no
figures. 
</P>
