Before Madikizela-Mandela's testimony today, more than 20
witnesses implicated her in a series of kidnappings and murders
in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the hearing, she conceded that "things went
horribly wrong" and said she was deeply sorry.
</P>
<P>
She made the announcement at an emotional plea from TRC
chairman Desmond Tutu.
</P>
<P>
Tutu, who described Madikizela-Mandela as "a great person",
said: "I beg you, I beg you, I beg you, please, I have not made
any particular finding about what happended. You are a great
person and you do not know your greatness will be enhanced if you
said 'sorry, things went horribly wrong.'"
</P>
<P>
Madikizela-Mandela, ex-wife of South African President Nelson
Mandela, is in bid for deputy presidency of the African National
Congress (ANC) at the ANC 50th national conference scheduled for
mid-December.
</P>
<P>
She is a member of the all-powerful ANC National Executive
Committee and president of the ANC Women's League. 
