<BODY>
<HEADLINE> N.Y. Stocks Edge Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street gave
back gains and ended mixed today as investors took a defensive
stance before Friday's key economic data.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 18.15 points to 8,050.16
and now stands about 200 points shy of its August 6 record of
8,259.31.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-6 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 632.15 million
shares as against Wednesday's hefty tally of 623.45 million.
</P>
<P>
The S&AMP;P 500 fell 3.67 to 973.10 after surrendering a 6.25 point
gain that would have beaten October 7's record close of 983.12 by
a thin margin.
</P>
<P>
The New York Stock Exchange composite index fell 0.72 to 509.43
after creeping within 1 point of record territory.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 1.71 to 1,613.42, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 3.30 to 665.80, but
the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 1.10 to 434.91.
</P>
</TEXT>
