<DOCNO> XIE19971205.0336 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Launches Investment Fund for Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The United States on
Thursday launched a 650 million U.S. fund to boost American
companies' investment in Africa.
</P>
<P>
George sunoz, head of the Overseas Private Investment
Corporation, said the launch of the fund showed "this region is
a priority for the U.S. private sector as well as the American
government."
</P>
<P>
U.S. trade with Africa has increased sharply in the past
several years, outpacing growth with all other areas of the
world. In 1996, it grew by 18.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The fund will support investments in natural resources,
telecommunications and manufacturing in 29 sub-Saharan nations.
Another fund, expected to be introduced early next year, will
provide 500 million U.S. dollars to support investments in African
infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's launch of the new fund is the result of Clinton
administration initiative to expand the economic relationship
between the United States and sub-Saharan Africa by lowering
tariffs, encouraging free-market reforms and urging international
lending organizations such as the World Bank and International
Monetary Fund to forgive some of the debts of the continent's
poorest countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
